  "commentary": "With SPX at 7136.71 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 7150, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that resistance level while providing stabilizing buying support on any dips. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX concentration between 7100-7200 creates a strong gravitational pull keeping price range-bound, with dealers acting as natural shock absorbers against large directional moves. Watch 7150 as the immediate ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, and 7100 as the key support floor where stabilizing buying emerges.\n\nBottom line: expect price to chop sideways between 7100-7150 with limited breakout potential.",
